"Triangulation" refers to using two sides of the middle-market finance theory triangle to help fully understand a point on the third side. Equity value is affected by the company's access to capital and the transfer methods available to the owner. Capital availability influences market value. For example, industries that cannot attract capital tend to suffer from depressed market values and vice versa.

