This chapter focuses on management transfers in corporate divestitures and buyouts from private owners. However, the motives of all players are similar, in that each wishes to maximize returns and minimize risk. In other words, each desires to play and win in the value world where it has maximum control, to finance at the optimal capital access point, and to utilize the most advantageous transfer methods.

