A two-step private auction is a more formal selling process than the one-step auction. A two-step auction process is most useful when the subject is so desirable that a formal auction process will not scare buyers away. Each step of the selling process is staged using deadlines. For instance, once a confidentiality agreement is executed and limited information is shared, the first stage calls for a written expression of interest. Only the top prospects are allowed to continue to the next step. In the second step, the prospects are allowed additional access to more detailed information about the target. Finally, the intermediary calls for a final offer, usually in the form of a formal letter of intent. The intermediary posts all rules for the two-step auction at the beginning of the process, complete with dates of completion for key events.

